{
  "text": "Indications for urgent TIPS positioning are persistent bleeding and refractory ascites unresponsive to combined endoscopic and pharmacological therapies. TIPS in children is recommended when: (1) surgical shunting is not feasible; (2) bad prognosis is predictable; (3) medical complications jeopardise surgical shunting outcome; and (4) end-stage liver failure requires a bridge to transplantation [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
  "correct_citation": {
